@Ravil Thanks for sharing it here. MQTT 5 with aliases could improve this, especially since the topic names in this test are relatively long - I used the topic tree from the ProveIt factory to have a real-world scenario - obfuscated (like Enterprise/UhiJiX/XsS/XVQhYa/VvAS/rUtziUBNSVTrkuyBv), but with the same topic levels and length. Interestingly, I have not yet seen that any of the tested brokers uses aliases when sending data to a subscribed client. While publishing with aliases works, either a) no broker has implemented it for subscriptions, or b) I’m doing something wrong.
Implementation could be challenging: for each connected client, the broker would need to maintain a mapping table, assign numbers to topics, and, when the max alias number is reached, decide whether to send the full topic name or reuse an existing number for a new topic. In theory, the broker would need to keep statistics to determine which topics benefit most from aliases and which do not.
